<BLOCK1><TI>STATEMENT OF CLAIM&mdash;<UNDER>AMENDED June 19<SUP>th</SUP>, 2018</UNDER></TI>
<P>1. The Plaintiffs, Marie Theresa Line Pettigrew and Linda Bernice Poole, (the &ldquo;Plaintiffs&rdquo;), both residing at Eastern Passage, in the Halifax Regional Municipality, Province of Nova Scotia; particularly, Pettigrew resides and owns property known as XXXXXXXXXX particularly, Poole resides and owns property know as XXXXXXXXXX;</P>
<P>2. The Defendant, Halifax Regional Water Commission, was created pursuant to the <EM>Halifax Regional Water Commission Act</EM>. Pursuant to this Act, the Halifax Regional Water Commission is a body corporate, and at all material times hereto was responsible for operation and maintenance of the Sanitary Sewer System for the said Halifax Regional Municipality;</P>
<P>3. On or about, the months of November and/or December, 2015, the Defendant carried out repairs in the connections (two) to the sewer system on account of similar malfunctions in the subject connections (known to it) and did it negligently causing a sewer backup in both of the residences of both Plaintiffs, there by causing them damages;</P>
<P>4. The Plaintiffs repeat the preceding paragraph and state that Halifax Regional Water Commission (the &ldquo;Defendant&rdquo;) owed a duty to carry out the work referred to in the paragraph immediately herein above, with care and in a workman-like manner <UNDER>and in such a way as to not cause a nuisance</UNDER>;</P>
<P>5. The Plaintiffs state that the Defendant, its agents and employees, negligently carried out the subject work. The particulars of the negligence are as follows:
<P1>(a) The Defendant failed to properly and adequately supervise the work to be carried out;</P1>
<P1>(b) The Defendant failed to warn the Plaintiffs, of the risk of a sewer backup;</P1>
<P1>(c) The Defendant failed in its duties in the proper management of the subject work;</P1>
<P1>(d) The Defendant failed in the training, handling and directing of its workers and agents to carry out the subject work;</P1>
<P1>(e) The Defendant failed, as it is statutorily bound to do, to employ staff and workers as is necessary to carry out its responsibilities in respect to the subject work;</P1>
<P1><UNDER>(f) The Defendant failed to carry out inspections during and after its subject work as a reasonable standard would call for in the carrying out of such work; and</UNDER></P1>
<P1><UNDER>(g)</UNDER> such other negligence as may appear.</P1></P>
<P>6. As a result of the work negligently carried out by the Defendant, the Plaintiffs suffered personal injuries, damages and loss, as a result of the raw sewage backing up into both of their respective residences both in their partially finished basements and on the main floor of both their residences.</P>
<P><UNDER>7. As a result of the work carried out by the Defendant, and the nuisance resulting there from, the Plaintiffs suffered personal injuries, damages and loss, as a result of the raw sewage backing up into both of their respective residences both in their partially finished basements and on the main floor of both their residences.</UNDER></P>
<P><UNDER>8. The Commission caused a nuisance as result of the subject repairs as referred to in paragraph 3, herein above.</UNDER></P>
<P><UNDER>9. The Plaintiffs repeat all the allegations in paragraph 5, in respect to the damages they claim due to the nuisance caused by the Defendant.</UNDER></P>
<P>10. The Plaintiffs plead <EM>res ipsa loquitur</EM>.</P>
<P><UNDER>11.</UNDER> The Plaintiff repeats the foregoing paragraphs and claims:
<P1>(a) general damages;</P1>
<P1>(b) special damages;</P1>
<P1><UNDER>(c) aggravated damages;</UNDER></P1>
<P1><UNDER>(d) punitive damages;</UNDER></P1>
<P1><UNDER>(e)</UNDER> prejudgment interest;</P1>
<P1><UNDER>(f)</UNDER> costs;</P1>
<P1><UNDER>(g)</UNDER> such other relief as this Honourable Court deems appropriate.</P1></P>
<P><BOLD>PLACE OF TRIAL</BOLD>: Halifax, Nova Scotia</P>
