<BLOCK1><TI TOCID="I"><UNDER>AMENDED</UNDER> STATEMENT OF DEFENCE</TI>
<P>1. This statement is made by the Defendant Halifax Regional Water Commission (&ldquo;Halifax Water&rdquo;).</P>
<P>2. Halifax Water admits the facts stated in paragraph 2 of the Statement of Claim.</P>
<P>3. Halifax Water neither admits nor denies allegations of fact about which it has insufficient knowledge to make an admission or a denial, and those allegations are contained in paragraph 1 of the Statement of Claim.</P>
<P>4. Except where otherwise stated herein, Halifax Water denies all other allegations of fact in the Statement of Claim.</P>
<P>5. On or about November 24, 2015, Halifax Water commenced a project to place sanitary sewer pipe in the area of Shore Road, Eastern Passage (the &ldquo;Project&rdquo;).</P>
<P>6. Following completion of the Project, the Plaintiffs notified Halifax Water of sewer backups at their respective properties. In response, Halifax Water excavated and made repairs to the sewer laterals in the area of the Plaintiffs' properties.</P>
<P>7. Halifax Water denies that it was negligent as described in paragraph 5 of the Statement of Claim, or otherwise, or at all.</P>
<P>8. <UNDER>Halifax Water further denies that it is liable to the Plaintiffs in nuisance as alleged in paragraphs 4, 7, and 8 of the Amended Statement of Claim, or otherwise, or at all, and puts the Plaintiffs to the strict proof thereof.</UNDER></P>
<P>9. Halifax Water pleads and relies on the <EM>Halifax Regional Water Commission Act</EM>, S.N.S. 2007, c. 55, as amended, (the &ldquo;<EM>Act</EM>&rdquo;) and associated rules and regulations and specifically pleads and relies on section 26 of the <EM>Act</EM>, <UNDER>and section 27A of the <EM>Act</EM>.</UNDER></P>
<P>10. Halifax Water states that it is not liable for damages caused by the maintenance, repair or breaking of its water systems unless the damages can be shown to be caused by Halifax Water's gross negligence. Halifax Water states that it has not been either negligent or grossly negligent.</P>
<P>11. Halifax Water denies that the Plaintiffs sustained the damages alleged and puts the Plaintiffs to the strict proof thereof.</P>
<P>12. <UNDER>Halifax Water denies that the Plaintiffs suffered personal injuries as alleged and puts the Plaintiffs to the strict proof thereof.</UNDER></P>
<P>13. <UNDER>Halifax Water further denies that the Plaintiffs are entitled to aggravated or punitive damages as claimed.</UNDER></P>
<P>14. Halifax Water pleads and relies upon the <EM>Tortfeasors Act</EM>, R.S.N.S. 1989, c. 471 and the <EM>Contributory Negligence Act</EM>, R.S.N.S. 1989, c. 95, both as amended.</P>
<P>15. Halifax Water further states that the Plaintiffs have failed to mitigate their damages.</P>
<P>16. Halifax Water repeats the foregoing and requests that this Action against it be dismissed with costs.</P>
